    <p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> This verse sets the stage for a refined analysis of faith. Arjuna does not reject devotion but seeks to understand its quality. By questioning the relationship between <em>śhraddhā</em> and <em>śhāstra</em>, he invites a deeper exploration into whether sincerity alone is enough, or whether clarity must guide sincerity to prevent deviation.</p>
